'''Eärendur''' (pron. {{IPA|[ˌe.aˈrendur]}}) was the fifteenth [[Lords of Andúnië|Lord of Andúnië]] in [[Númenor]]<ref name=Tar-Palantir/> in the days of king [[Ar-Sakalthôr]].<ref name=Akallabeth>{{S|Akallabeth}}</ref> Eärendur was the brother of [[Lindórië]], who would be the grandmother of the wise King [[Tar-Palantir]].<ref name=Tar-Palantir/><ref name=Akallabeth/>

As Lord of [[Andúnië]], Eärendur was also the ancestor of the Kings of [[Gondor]] and [[Arnor]] in [[Middle-earth]]. [[Aragorn|Aragorn II]] was his direct descendant through no less than forty-four generations.

==Etymology==
''Eärendur'' is a [[Quenya]] name. It means "(professional) mariner".<ref>{{L|297|118}}</ref> As Paul Strack explains, a more literal translation might be "Servant of the Sea". It is a compound of [[eär]] ("sea") and [[-ndur|-(n)dur]] ("servant").<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://www.eldamo.org/content/words/word-656453537.html|articlename=Q. ''Eärendur'' m.|website=Eldamo|accessed=29 October 2021}}</ref>

